  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A creature that fails its Reflex save to avoid a noose snare may not move from its current location and is unable to breathe unless it succeeds on a Strength or Escape Artist check against the trap&#8217;s DC or destroys the trap via damage. For every 4 ranks in Craft (traps) you possess, an affected creature is treated as though an additional round passed each round it remains in the snare for the purposes of how long they can hold their breath. Additionally, any spell the creature attempts to cast suffers a 50% spell failure chance if it requires verbal components.</p>\n",
